Each function in the object that is being passed as the first argument in async.parallel is being passed a callback argument. I'm learning about callbacks and how they work. If this were SQL, here is what I am trying to do:
Here is what we have that is not working with the MongoDB driver:

,@user3399551: The difference is that the Fisher-Yates algorithm only picks an item to the left (or the same item) instead of an item in the entire array. Notice the `* i` instead of `* 49` in the random number. On the page that I linked to about the Fisher-Yates algorithm is an explanation of why it's biased if you swap with any item in the array, in the section ""Implementation errors"". Regarding the numbers not being repeated

the array starts with the numbers 1 to 49, if you swap two of them it still has the numbers 1 to 49 only in a different order. There are no duplicates introduced.","Embed Field: Get all items where subDocument.value in listOfStrings
